Who was George HW Bush?Bush Sr's single presidential term in office was defined by foreign policy, at a time when communism was collapsing in Eastern Europe.Despite achieving popularity ratings of 90%, Bush was accused of neglecting domestic affairs and was defeated by Bill Clinton in the 1992 election. His popularity suffered after he went back on a promise not to raise taxes. George HW Bush: Life in picturesBush entered politics in 1964 after starting a Texan oil business and becoming a millionaire by the age of 40. During World War Two, he was an aviator before being shot down by the Japanese in September 1944 while on a bombing raid.Following his honourable discharge from the navy in 1945, Bush married then 18-year-old Barbara Pierce. Their marriage would last 73 years and they would have six children together.He is survived by five of his children and their spouses, 17 grandchildren, eight great-grandchildren and two siblings.
